CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 5, 1969, pg. 16, reads: " Leaving Church - Mr. and Mrs. James C. White smile happily as they drive away from the United Brushton Methodist Church following their recent wedding. The bride is the former Catheleen Clark, daughter of Mr. and Mrs. Wallie Clark of Homewood.  The newlyweds are attended by Lillian Mellerson and Donald Francher.  A reception at the Wilkinsburg Firemen's Club Room followed the ceremony. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Groom James C. White and bride Catheleen Clark White, seated in back of car after wedding ceremony at United Brushton Methodist Church
